{{Han etym}}
Originally {{liushu|p|adj=1|nocap=1}} in the oracle bone script. The ancient Chinese regarded the rainbow as a two-headed creature.

In the seal script, it has become a {{Han compound|虫|工|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=p|t1=insect; creature|nocap=1}}.

